&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a business-minded Portfolio Manager to act as a leader with a 360° view of assigned categories and countries. You will drive strategy, manage a diverse portfolio, and collaborate across teams to ensure growth and profitability in your region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The e-commerce landscape is shifting fast. We are looking for someone with a growth mindset, data-driven curiosity, and the willingness to learn and adapt on the go. We value energy, potential, and the courage to look for smarter, modern ways of doing things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remuneration starts at 1900 €/month gross + variable part&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;What you will do:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute end-to-end category strategies, set pricing, and drive commercial objectives as the primary business owner for your markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the lifecycle of our products, making key decisions on launches, maintenance, and phase-outs based on performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the forecasting cycle, ensuring accuracy by incorporating market trends, seasonality, and local variables with the help of modern data tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate market insights into product briefs for development and support content localization to ensure it resonates with local customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Operations to optimize costs and inventory, and work with Marketing to boost category visibility across digital channels (Google, Meta, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What your typical day will actually look like:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;30–40% Analytics &amp;amp; Performance Review: Diving into sales data, margins, pricing, stock levels, forecasts, and market trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;25–30% Team Coordination: Acting as a bridge and working closely with Marketing, Operations, Content, Product, and Sales teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20–25% Strategic &amp;amp; Category Decisions: Shaping product lifecycles, pricing setups, launches, phase-outs, and specific country plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10–15% Content &amp;amp; Market Localization: Ensuring our products and campaigns fit local customers perfectly (and yes, this is where your tech-forward approach and AI tools will save you heaps of time).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
